1
00:00:19,188 --> 00:00:20,814
<i>My name is Max.</i>

2
00:00:21,857 --> 00:00:24,276
<i>My world is fire and blood.</i>

3
00:00:25,152 --> 00:00:26,695
<i>Why are you hurting these people?</i>

4
00:00:26,945 --> 00:00:28,280
<i>It's the oil, stupid.</i>

5
00:00:28,530 --> 00:00:30,991
<i>- Oil wars.
- We are killing for guzzoline.</i>

6
00:00:31,241 --> 00:00:32,910
<i>The world is running out of water.</i>

7
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:34,912
<i>Now there's the water wars.</i>

8
00:00:36,622 --> 00:00:38,999
<i>Once, I was a cop.</i>

9
00:00:39,249 --> 00:00:41,793
<i>A road warrior searching
for a righteous cause.</i>

10
00:00:42,044 --> 00:00:43,629
<i>to the terminal freak-out point.</i>

11
00:00:43,879 --> 00:00:46,965
<i>Mankind has gone rogue,
terrorizing itself.</i>

12
00:00:47,216 --> 00:00:48,550
<i>Thermonuclear skirmish.</i>

13
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:49,968
<i>The earth is sour.</i>

14
00:00:50,219 --> 00:00:51,470
<i>Our bones are poisoned.</i>

15
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:53,680
<i>We have become half-life.</i>

16
00:00:54,723 --> 00:00:56,558
<i>As the world fell...</i>

17
00:00:56,808 --> 00:00:59,728
<i>...each of us, in our own way,
was broken.</i>

18
00:01:00,270 --> 00:01:03,440
<i>It was hard to know who was more crazy:</i>

19
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,610
<i>Me...</i>

20
00:01:06,985 --> 00:01:08,737
<i>...or everyone else.</i>

21
00:01:11,406 --> 00:01:12,574
<i>Hello?</i>

22
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:16,620
<i>Where are you?</i>

23
00:01:24,044 --> 00:01:25,170
<i>Where are you, Max?</i>

24
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:27,381
<i>- Here they come again.
- Max Rockatansky.</i>

25
00:01:27,631 --> 00:01:30,801
<i>Worming their way
into the black matter of my brain.</i>

26
00:01:31,051 --> 00:01:33,053
<i>- Help us, Max.
- You promised to help us.</i>

27
00:01:37,349 --> 00:01:39,226
<i>I tell myself...</i>

28
00:01:39,476 --> 00:01:41,561
<i>...they cannot touch me.</i>

29
00:01:43,438 --> 00:01:45,232
<i>They are long dead.</i>

30
00:02:43,123 --> 00:02:44,166
<i>I am the one...</i>

31
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:47,502
<i>...who runs from both
the living and the dead.</i>

32
00:02:48,628 --> 00:02:50,922
<i>Hunted by scavengers.</i>

33
00:02:51,631 --> 00:02:54,468
<i>Haunted by those I could not protect.</i>

34
00:03:03,852 --> 00:03:06,355
<i>So I exist in this wasteland.</i>

35
00:03:11,401 --> 00:03:15,405
<i>A man reduced to a single instinct:</i>

36
00:03:16,156 --> 00:03:17,574
<i>Survive.</i>

37
00:04:38,071 --> 00:04:38,904
Max?

38
00:04:39,114 --> 00:04:39,990
Is that you?

39
00:04:41,158 --> 00:04:41,992
Where were you?

40
00:04:44,161 --> 00:04:46,079
Help us. Where were you?

41
00:04:46,329 --> 00:04:47,162
Where were you, Max?

42
00:05:04,097 --> 00:05:05,098
Where were you, Max?

43
00:05:05,724 --> 00:05:06,557
Stop running.

44
00:05:07,476 --> 00:05:08,518
You let us die!

45
00:05:10,061 --> 00:05:11,438
You let us die!

46
00:05:11,688 --> 00:05:12,898
You let us die!

47
00:05:13,773 --> 00:05:14,733
You promised to help us!

48
00:05:14,941 --> 00:05:15,774
Why?

49
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:36,171
Witness!

50
00:05:38,298 --> 00:05:39,591
I got him.

51
00:06:29,140 --> 00:06:30,809
We are War Boys!

52
00:06:31,059 --> 00:06:31,977
War Boys!

53
00:06:32,227 --> 00:06:34,062
Kamakrazee War Boys!

54
00:06:34,312 --> 00:06:35,145
War Boys!

55
00:06:35,355 --> 00:06:37,482
Fucacima kamakrazee...

56
00:06:37,732 --> 00:06:39,025
...War Boys!

57
00:06:39,276 --> 00:06:41,236
Hooked on!

58
00:06:42,028 --> 00:06:42,908
Today we're heading...

59
00:06:43,154 --> 00:06:44,489
...to Gas Town!

60
00:06:44,739 --> 00:06:46,074
Gas Town!

61
00:06:46,324 --> 00:06:48,326
Today we're hauling Aqua Cola.

62
00:06:48,994 --> 00:06:50,370
Aqua Cola!

63
00:06:50,787 --> 00:06:53,415
- Today we're hauling produce!
- Produce!

64
00:06:53,832 --> 00:06:55,083
And today we're hauling...

65
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:56,543
...Mother's Milk!

66
00:06:56,793 --> 00:06:58,295
Mother's Milk!

67
00:07:23,028 --> 00:07:26,489
<i>Joe! Joe! Joe! Immortan Joe!</i>

68
00:07:47,177 --> 00:07:49,387
Rev it up for the Immortan Joe!

69
00:07:58,647 --> 00:08:02,651
Once again, we send off my War Rig
to bring back...

70
00:08:02,901 --> 00:08:05,236
...guzzoline from Gas Town...

71
00:08:05,487 --> 00:08:08,239
...and bullets from the Bullet Farm!

72
00:08:08,782 --> 00:08:12,452
Once again, I salute my Imperator...

73
00:08:12,702 --> 00:08:14,329
...Furiosa!

74
00:08:14,579 --> 00:08:15,497
And I salute...

75
00:08:15,747 --> 00:08:18,375
...my half-life War Boys...

76
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:20,960
...who will ride with me eternal...

77
00:08:21,252 --> 00:08:23,588
...on the highways of Valhalla.

78
00:08:23,838 --> 00:08:26,216
<i>V8! V8! V8! V8!</i>

79
00:08:26,466 --> 00:08:29,094
I am your redeemer.

80
00:08:29,344 --> 00:08:31,680
It is by my hand...

81
00:08:31,930 --> 00:08:34,974
...you will rise from the ashes...

82
00:08:35,225 --> 00:08:36,184
...of this world!

83
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:46,820
It's coming. Get ready.

84
00:08:47,070 --> 00:08:51,032
Yes. Yes. Yes. It's coming.

85
00:09:47,672 --> 00:09:49,716
Do not, my friends...

86
00:09:49,966 --> 00:09:52,093
...become addicted to water.

87
00:09:52,343 --> 00:09:53,928
It will take hold of you...

88
00:09:54,262 --> 00:09:57,140
...and you will resent its absence.

89
00:10:22,040 --> 00:10:23,500
Clear off!

90
00:10:25,168 --> 00:10:27,086
Get them all off!

91
00:10:27,629 --> 00:10:28,630
Clear off!

92
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:30,673
Get them all off.

93
00:10:31,591 --> 00:10:33,760
Get off!

94
00:10:38,223 --> 00:10:41,184
Signal Gas Town. Convoy's on its way.

95
00:11:07,752 --> 00:11:08,585
I got a War Boy...

96
00:11:08,628 --> 00:11:10,380
...running on empty.

97
00:11:10,964 --> 00:11:12,674
Hook up that full-life.

98
00:11:16,886 --> 00:11:18,930
Hey! Careful. That's a universal donor.

99
00:12:16,446 --> 00:12:18,531
Boss, we're not going to Gas Town?

100
00:12:20,992 --> 00:12:22,452
Bullet Farm?

101
00:12:24,829 --> 00:12:26,497
We're heading east.

102
00:12:28,249 --> 00:12:30,251
I'll pass it down the line.

103
00:12:31,085 --> 00:12:32,378
New orders!

104
00:12:32,629 --> 00:12:34,297
Thunder up! Thunder up!

105
00:12:34,714 --> 00:12:36,007
This is not a supply run!

106
00:12:37,008 --> 00:12:37,967
Go. Go.

107
00:12:38,217 --> 00:12:40,762
- Ace, what's going on?
- Go. We're heading east.

108
00:12:41,012 --> 00:12:43,389
- Why?
- I don't know. That's the order.

109
00:13:01,407 --> 00:13:02,240
Moo.

110
00:13:02,283 --> 00:13:03,326
Hey, Pa.

111
00:13:03,576 --> 00:13:05,119
You know about this?

112
00:13:05,954 --> 00:13:08,539
Your produce ain't going to Gas Town.

113
00:13:18,174 --> 00:13:20,009
She's gone off-road...

114
00:13:20,426 --> 00:13:22,303
...into hostile territory.

115
00:13:24,472 --> 00:13:25,556
Why would she do that?

116
00:13:27,850 --> 00:13:28,683
Let me see.

117
00:13:28,726 --> 00:13:29,559
Rictus.

118
00:13:29,686 --> 00:13:31,145
- I wanna see.
- Rictus.

119
00:13:31,396 --> 00:13:33,648
Go see what's agitating Dad.

120
00:14:01,634 --> 00:14:03,219
Splendid!

121
00:14:04,387 --> 00:14:06,097
Angharad!

122
00:14:15,606 --> 00:14:16,566
Where are they?

123
00:14:16,816 --> 00:14:18,651
They are not your property.

124
00:14:18,901 --> 00:14:19,734
Miss Giddy?

125
00:14:20,111 --> 00:14:21,696
You cannot own a human being.

126
00:14:23,114 --> 00:14:25,158
Sooner or later someone pushes back!

127
00:14:25,408 --> 00:14:27,493
Where is she taking them?

128
00:14:27,744 --> 00:14:29,954
She didn't take them.
They begged her to go!

129
00:14:32,040 --> 00:14:33,499
Where is she taking them?

130
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:35,543
A long way from you.

131
00:15:00,777 --> 00:15:03,029
Hey. Hey, what's happening?

132
00:15:05,156 --> 00:15:06,324
Slit!

133
00:15:06,991 --> 00:15:08,493
What's going on? Slit!

134
00:15:08,743 --> 00:15:11,454
Treason. Betrayal.
An Imperator gone rogue.

135
00:15:11,704 --> 00:15:12,537
An Imperator.

136
00:15:12,622 --> 00:15:13,206
Who?

137
00:15:13,456 --> 00:15:16,292
Furiosa! She took a lot of stuff
from Immortan Joe.

138
00:15:16,542 --> 00:15:17,376
What stuff?

139
00:15:17,835 --> 00:15:19,754
Breeders! His prize breeders!

140
00:15:20,004 --> 00:15:22,507
He wants them back!
Not a hand laid on them.

141
00:15:29,430 --> 00:15:31,390
By my deeds I honor him.

142
00:15:31,641 --> 00:15:32,725
V8.

143
00:15:36,312 --> 00:15:38,314
<i>V8! V8! V8!</i>

144
00:15:44,737 --> 00:15:45,570
That's my wheel.

145
00:15:45,738 --> 00:15:46,571
I'm driving.

146
00:15:46,781 --> 00:15:47,740
You're my lancer.

147
00:15:47,990 --> 00:15:49,367
I just promoted myself.

148
00:15:49,784 --> 00:15:51,160
Not today. Today is my day.

149
00:15:51,410 --> 00:15:52,243
Look at you.

150
00:15:52,453 --> 00:15:54,288
If you can't stand up, you can't do war.

151
00:15:54,539 --> 00:15:55,790
He's right, son.

152
00:15:56,040 --> 00:15:58,209
I'm not staying here dying soft.

153
00:15:58,501 --> 00:15:59,961
You're already a corpse.

154
00:16:00,211 --> 00:16:02,380
- I just need a top-up. More juice.
- No time!

155
00:16:03,131 --> 00:16:04,173
We take my Blood Bag.

156
00:16:04,423 --> 00:16:06,663
We take my Blood Bag
and strap him to the lancer's perch.

157
00:16:06,884 --> 00:16:08,427
It's got a muzzle on it. It's feral.

158
00:16:08,678 --> 00:16:09,262
That's right.

159
00:16:09,512 --> 00:16:11,722
High-octane crazy blood filling me up.

160
00:16:16,811 --> 00:16:17,687
If I'm gonna die...

161
00:16:19,105 --> 00:16:21,107
...I'm gonna die historic
on the Fury Road.

162
00:16:27,613 --> 00:16:29,532
Yeah. Yeah.

163
00:16:29,782 --> 00:16:33,035
Organic, hitch up his Blood Bag.

164
00:16:33,452 --> 00:16:34,495
Right-o.

165
00:16:44,505 --> 00:16:46,174
How much more can they take from me?

166
00:16:46,424 --> 00:16:48,634
They've got my blood. Now it's my car!

167
00:17:26,714 --> 00:17:27,715
Immortan!

168
00:17:29,091 --> 00:17:30,593
Immortan Joe!

169
00:17:33,512 --> 00:17:34,931
He looked at me!

170
00:17:35,556 --> 00:17:38,434
- He looked right at me!
- He looked at your Blood Bag!

171
00:17:38,684 --> 00:17:40,978
He turned his head.
He looked me in the eye.

172
00:17:41,229 --> 00:17:43,397
He was scanning the horizon.

173
00:17:43,814 --> 00:17:44,899
No.

174
00:17:45,233 --> 00:17:46,317
I am awaited.

175
00:17:46,859 --> 00:17:48,945
I am awaited in Valhalla!

176
00:17:51,447 --> 00:17:53,532
<i>Confucamus!</i>

177
00:17:55,952 --> 00:17:56,994
Immortan!

178
00:17:58,371 --> 00:17:59,872
Yeah!

179
00:18:19,225 --> 00:18:21,018
Hey! Heads up!

180
00:18:21,269 --> 00:18:22,228
Heads up!

181
00:18:27,108 --> 00:18:28,109
Boss!

182
00:18:29,068 --> 00:18:30,388
We got vehicles from the Citadel.

183
00:18:30,611 --> 00:18:31,612
They're firing flares.

184
00:18:32,238 --> 00:18:33,590
They want reinforcements from Gas Town...

185
00:18:33,614 --> 00:18:35,199
...and the Bullet Farm.

186
00:18:35,449 --> 00:18:36,282
What is this?

187
00:18:36,450 --> 00:18:37,785
Backup? Decoy?

188
00:18:39,161 --> 00:18:40,705
It's a detour.

189
00:19:12,862 --> 00:19:13,863
Eyes right!

190
00:19:17,199 --> 00:19:18,284
Buzzards!

191
00:19:18,534 --> 00:19:21,454
- Buzzards right! Eyes on! Eyes on!
- Buzzards right!

192
00:19:21,704 --> 00:19:22,788
- Eyes on!
- Eyes on!

193
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:28,627
Should we turn it around
and run them into our backup?

194
00:19:30,296 --> 00:19:31,839
No! We're good!

195
00:19:32,798 --> 00:19:34,050
We fang it!

196
00:19:37,470 --> 00:19:39,513
Thunder up! Here we go!

197
00:19:42,641 --> 00:19:44,435
Prepare the gunners!

198
00:20:13,881 --> 00:20:14,714
Morsov!

199
00:20:18,052 --> 00:20:19,011
Come on, attack!

200
00:20:31,899 --> 00:20:32,732
War!

201
00:20:41,409 --> 00:20:42,701
Ready!

202
00:21:26,829 --> 00:21:28,372
She's ours, Slit!

203
00:21:28,622 --> 00:21:29,455
She's ours.

204
00:21:29,498 --> 00:21:31,917
First, we get the Buzzards off her back!

205
00:21:38,007 --> 00:21:38,840
Form up!

206
00:21:43,095 --> 00:21:44,180
That's my head!

207
00:22:19,507 --> 00:22:21,550
Get up! You can do it!

208
00:22:26,722 --> 00:22:27,806
Morsov!

209
00:22:29,266 --> 00:22:31,352
- Morsov!
- No!

210
00:22:31,602 --> 00:22:33,312
- Witness me!
- Witness!

211
00:22:33,562 --> 00:22:34,396
Witness!

212
00:22:39,985 --> 00:22:41,070
Fly!

213
00:22:45,658 --> 00:22:46,491
Witness!

214
00:22:46,617 --> 00:22:47,450
Witness!

215
00:22:48,994 --> 00:22:50,996
Mediocre, Morsov!

216
00:22:51,247 --> 00:22:53,457
- Mediocre!
- Hoorah!

217
00:23:24,154 --> 00:23:24,987
Get ready!

218
00:23:26,865 --> 00:23:27,866
Back me in!

219
00:23:32,162 --> 00:23:33,247
They're coming!

220
00:23:50,973 --> 00:23:52,975
We can't breathe down there!

221
00:23:53,225 --> 00:23:54,101
Stay out of sight!

222
00:23:55,185 --> 00:23:56,018
Now!

223
00:24:08,490 --> 00:24:09,491
Go back!

224
00:24:10,826 --> 00:24:11,410
Where's he going?

225
00:24:11,660 --> 00:24:12,244
Hydraulics!

226
00:24:12,494 --> 00:24:13,454
Hydraulics!

227
00:24:35,684 --> 00:24:36,810
Yeah.

228
00:24:41,940 --> 00:24:44,151
Now we bring home the booty.

229
00:25:10,636 --> 00:25:12,680
She thinks she can lose us, Dad.

230
00:25:12,930 --> 00:25:14,765
She thinks we're stupid.

231
00:25:15,140 --> 00:25:17,393
She thinks she can lose us in there!

232
00:25:36,161 --> 00:25:37,037
Fang it!

233
00:25:37,746 --> 00:25:39,039
Fang it!

234
00:25:45,129 --> 00:25:46,130
Why can't you stop?

235
00:25:48,090 --> 00:25:49,133
Crew! Out of the way!

236
00:25:49,383 --> 00:25:50,216
Out of the way!

237
00:25:50,342 --> 00:25:51,552
What have you done?

238
00:25:51,802 --> 00:25:52,928
What have you done?

239
00:25:56,807 --> 00:25:57,640
Yeah.

240
00:26:15,075 --> 00:26:17,235
We need counterweight.
Get the Blood Bag down the back.

241
00:26:28,172 --> 00:26:30,507
Hunt them down! Hunt them down!

242
00:26:56,450 --> 00:26:57,326
Hey, head!

243
00:26:57,576 --> 00:26:58,744
Say bye-bye to the neck!

244
00:27:00,204 --> 00:27:01,037
We're going in!

245
00:28:03,767 --> 00:28:06,353
Come on! We've almost got her!

246
00:28:14,820 --> 00:28:16,488
Come on! Hold it steady!

247
00:28:44,641 --> 00:28:45,474
Oh, what a day!

248
00:28:45,559 --> 00:28:47,311
What a lovely day!

249
00:29:06,955 --> 00:29:07,788
I am the man...

250
00:29:08,916 --> 00:29:10,125
...who grabs the sun...

251
00:29:12,961 --> 00:29:14,671
...riding to Valhalla!

252
00:29:17,549 --> 00:29:18,133
Witness me...

253
00:29:18,383 --> 00:29:19,216
...Blood Bag!

254
00:29:23,430 --> 00:29:24,848
Witness!

255
00:29:48,830 --> 00:29:50,999
I live, I die, I live again!

256
00:33:34,055 --> 00:33:35,473
We're not going back.

257
00:34:04,336 --> 00:34:05,169
Water.

258
00:35:01,184 --> 00:35:02,017
You.

259
00:35:17,242 --> 00:35:19,703
Angharad, is that just the wind...

260
00:35:20,370 --> 00:35:22,122
...or is that a furious vexation?

261
00:36:51,836 --> 00:36:53,046
I got it!

262
00:37:34,462 --> 00:37:37,424
Glory me, Blood Bag!
We snagged her alive.

263
00:37:37,674 --> 00:37:40,009
He's gonna shred her. Shred her.

264
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:41,594
Bolt cutters.

265
00:37:42,178 --> 00:37:43,263
Chain.

266
00:37:44,973 --> 00:37:46,099
Hey, hey!

267
00:37:49,686 --> 00:37:51,396
Oh, look at them.

268
00:37:51,855 --> 00:37:54,232
So shiny. So chrome.

269
00:37:54,691 --> 00:37:55,942
He's gonna be so grateful.

270
00:37:56,985 --> 00:37:58,403
We could ask for anything.

271
00:37:59,487 --> 00:38:01,239
I wanna drive the War Rig.

272
00:38:02,490 --> 00:38:04,451
- What are you gonna ask for?
- That's my jacket.

273
00:38:04,701 --> 00:38:06,411
Heh, heh. Sure.

274
00:38:07,078 --> 00:38:10,248
- You can ask for more than a jacket.
- We're going to the Green Place.

275
00:38:10,498 --> 00:38:12,208
Wait, it's you and me. Ugh!

276
00:38:25,847 --> 00:38:28,308
We're going to the Green Place
of Many Mothers.

277
00:38:46,868 --> 00:38:48,453
How does it feel?

278
00:38:48,703 --> 00:38:50,872
- It hurts.
- Out here, everything hurts.

279
00:38:53,958 --> 00:38:55,502
You wanna get through this?

280
00:38:59,214 --> 00:39:00,215
Do as I say.

281
00:39:05,595 --> 00:39:07,472
Now pick up what you can and run.

282
00:39:14,270 --> 00:39:15,271
Tsa!

283
00:39:50,056 --> 00:39:51,474
Kill switches.

284
00:39:53,059 --> 00:39:54,644
I set the sequence myself.

285
00:39:54,894 --> 00:39:56,813
This Rig goes nowhere without me.

286
00:40:00,650 --> 00:40:01,943
You can get in.

287
00:40:03,319 --> 00:40:04,737
Not without them.

288
00:40:13,162 --> 00:40:14,330
So we wait.

289
00:40:23,214 --> 00:40:25,675
You're relying on the gratitude
of a very bad man.

290
00:40:25,925 --> 00:40:28,886
You've damaged one of his wives.
How grateful do you think he's gonna be?

291
00:40:36,019 --> 00:40:39,188
You're sitting on 2000 horsepower
of nitro-boosted war machine.

292
00:40:40,148 --> 00:40:42,525
I'd say you got
about a five-minute head start.

293
00:40:50,742 --> 00:40:52,327
You want that thing off your face?

294
00:41:05,173 --> 00:41:06,215
Let's go.

295
00:41:50,718 --> 00:41:54,263
Of all the legs you had to shoot,
that one was attached to his favorite.

296
00:42:14,951 --> 00:42:15,952
Smeg!

297
00:42:36,431 --> 00:42:38,200
You don't have to do it
just because he tells you.

298
00:42:38,224 --> 00:42:40,744
- What choice does she have?
- He's not gonna hurt us. He needs us.

299
00:42:40,768 --> 00:42:41,686
- Why?
- To bargain.

300
00:42:41,936 --> 00:42:42,937
Oh, he'll hurt us.

301
00:42:43,187 --> 00:42:44,939
Think he's coming to the Green Place?

302
00:42:45,189 --> 00:42:46,269
Never! He's a crazy smeg...

303
00:42:46,482 --> 00:42:48,109
...who eats schlanger!

304
00:43:14,844 --> 00:43:15,928
Nah, stay out of there.

305
00:43:16,179 --> 00:43:17,263
Behind you.

306
00:43:22,101 --> 00:43:23,561
The Gas Town Boys.

307
00:43:25,354 --> 00:43:27,190
Don't damage the goods.

308
00:43:33,696 --> 00:43:35,114
What do you see?

309
00:43:37,450 --> 00:43:38,868
Big Rigs...

310
00:43:40,578 --> 00:43:41,954
...Polecats...

311
00:43:42,663 --> 00:43:43,748
...Flamers...

312
00:43:45,583 --> 00:43:48,169
...and there's the People Eater himself.

313
00:43:49,295 --> 00:43:51,297
Coming to count the cost.

314
00:44:07,396 --> 00:44:09,565
We're dragging something out back.

315
00:44:09,816 --> 00:44:11,150
I think it's the fuel pod.

316
00:44:12,026 --> 00:44:12,860
No, no.

317
00:44:14,403 --> 00:44:15,236
I'll go.

318
00:45:39,322 --> 00:45:40,823
Filth! You traitored him!

319
00:45:45,661 --> 00:45:46,913
No unnecessary killing!

320
00:45:47,163 --> 00:45:48,956
- This War Boy wants me dead!
- We agreed!

321
00:45:49,624 --> 00:45:51,500
He's kamakrazee!

322
00:45:51,959 --> 00:45:53,961
He's just a kid
at the end of his half-life!

323
00:45:54,211 --> 00:45:56,255
No! I live. I die. I live again!

324
00:45:57,006 --> 00:45:58,549
- Hold him!
- Tie him up!

325
00:45:58,799 --> 00:45:59,675
Throw him out!

326
00:46:00,134 --> 00:46:01,260
Chuck him out!

327
00:46:02,386 --> 00:46:04,055
You got more friends.

328
00:46:06,390 --> 00:46:07,808
Bullet Farmer.

329
00:46:08,059 --> 00:46:10,227
- They're coming from the Bullet Farm.
- Yeah?

330
00:46:11,354 --> 00:46:13,147
It's over. You can't defy him.

331
00:46:13,522 --> 00:46:14,398
Just watch us, mate!

332
00:46:14,649 --> 00:46:15,482
He is the one...

333
00:46:15,691 --> 00:46:18,011
- ...who grabbed the sun.
- Look how slick he's fooled you.

334
00:46:18,069 --> 00:46:19,629
- He's a lying old man.
- By his hand...

335
00:46:19,862 --> 00:46:21,742
- ...we'll be lifted up!
- That's why we have...

336
00:46:21,948 --> 00:46:23,491
...his logo seared on our backs!

337
00:46:23,741 --> 00:46:25,368
"Breeding Stock!" "Battle Fodder!"

338
00:46:25,618 --> 00:46:26,535
No, I am awaited!

339
00:46:26,786 --> 00:46:29,146
- You're an old man's "Battle Fodder"!
- Killing everyone...

340
00:46:29,330 --> 00:46:30,970
- ...and everything.
- We're not to blame!

341
00:46:31,457 --> 00:46:32,792
Then who killed the world?

342
00:47:00,945 --> 00:47:02,905
I made a deal up ahead. Safe passage.

343
00:47:03,739 --> 00:47:05,491
I don't know if it's still any good.

344
00:47:06,325 --> 00:47:07,368
Get back in the hold!

345
00:47:07,618 --> 00:47:09,161
Keep the hatch open.

346
00:47:16,377 --> 00:47:17,420
I need you here.

347
00:47:19,797 --> 00:47:21,298
You may have to drive the Rig.

348
00:47:26,804 --> 00:47:27,637
You.

349
00:47:28,889 --> 00:47:29,932
You stay.

350
00:47:31,142 --> 00:47:32,226
You stay there.

351
00:47:35,813 --> 00:47:38,190
Whatever you do, you can't be seen.

352
00:47:38,441 --> 00:47:40,234
I'm supposed to be alone.

353
00:47:40,484 --> 00:47:41,986
That was the deal.

354
00:47:48,617 --> 00:47:49,785
Down here.

355
00:48:10,681 --> 00:48:11,515
Hey.

356
00:48:12,641 --> 00:48:13,809
What's your name?

357
00:48:15,686 --> 00:48:16,687
What do I call you?

358
00:48:18,147 --> 00:48:19,273
Does it matter?

359
00:48:21,692 --> 00:48:22,735
Fine.

360
00:48:23,277 --> 00:48:24,361
When I yell "fool"...

361
00:48:24,612 --> 00:48:26,906
...you drive out of here
as fast as you can.

362
00:48:28,741 --> 00:48:30,034
This is the sequence:

363
00:48:30,868 --> 00:48:32,495
One. One, two.

364
00:48:32,745 --> 00:48:33,788
One.

365
00:48:34,455 --> 00:48:36,874
Red. Black. Go.

366
00:48:37,583 --> 00:48:38,793
You have it?

367
00:50:04,336 --> 00:50:05,754
It's all here!

368
00:50:07,006 --> 00:50:09,967
Three thousand gallons of guzzoline,
just like you asked!

369
00:50:14,013 --> 00:50:15,723
I'm gonna unhitch the pod.

370
00:50:17,725 --> 00:50:19,226
You drop the rocks.

371
00:50:27,860 --> 00:50:29,153
You said:

372
00:50:29,403 --> 00:50:30,863
"A few vehicles in pursuit.

373
00:50:31,363 --> 00:50:32,573
Maybe."

374
00:50:32,907 --> 00:50:34,033
We count three War Parties!

375
00:50:36,118 --> 00:50:37,786
Yeah, well, I got unlucky.

376
00:50:38,370 --> 00:50:39,747
Let's do this!

377
00:51:06,690 --> 00:51:07,523
Fool!

378
00:51:48,440 --> 00:51:49,775
That's our fuel!

379
00:52:04,540 --> 00:52:06,500
Make way for the Ripsaw!

380
00:52:10,796 --> 00:52:11,964
Come on! Move them!

381
00:52:21,682 --> 00:52:22,808
Once I'm over...

382
00:52:23,058 --> 00:52:25,269
...clear the rocks
and bring everyone through.

383
00:52:25,519 --> 00:52:26,478
Immortan!

384
00:52:27,271 --> 00:52:28,772
Immortan Joe!

385
00:52:29,023 --> 00:52:32,276
I got a War Boy!
Says he was on the War Rig.

386
00:52:34,695 --> 00:52:36,572
You! Climb aboard!

387
00:52:38,699 --> 00:52:40,075
Hey. Hey!

388
00:52:41,076 --> 00:52:42,286
I got his boot!

389
00:52:42,536 --> 00:52:44,538
I got the Blood Bag's boot!

390
00:52:45,039 --> 00:52:46,457
Take me!

391
00:52:46,832 --> 00:52:48,292
I got his boot!

392
00:52:50,419 --> 00:52:52,921
All this for a family squabble.

393
00:52:53,672 --> 00:52:55,591
Healthy babies.

394
00:55:03,886 --> 00:55:04,845
Reload the clip.

395
00:55:05,512 --> 00:55:06,345
I can't.

396
00:55:13,437 --> 00:55:14,270
Gun!

397
00:55:15,939 --> 00:55:16,772
Gimme the gun!

398
00:55:16,857 --> 00:55:17,441
Not loaded yet!

399
00:55:17,691 --> 00:55:18,524
Now!

400
00:55:18,567 --> 00:55:19,400
We had a deal!

401
00:56:08,408 --> 00:56:09,618
Rictus!

402
00:56:10,077 --> 00:56:11,119
The wives!

403
00:56:11,370 --> 00:56:12,704
No more flames.

404
00:56:19,378 --> 00:56:20,712
Splendid!

405
00:56:21,213 --> 00:56:22,339
Splendid!

406
00:56:22,589 --> 00:56:23,465
That's my child!

407
00:56:25,175 --> 00:56:26,093
My property!

408
00:56:28,178 --> 00:56:29,012
Immorta--

409
00:56:38,730 --> 00:56:42,609
Immortan. If I get on the Rig,
there's a way inside.

410
00:56:42,859 --> 00:56:44,820
- What is your name?
- It's Nux.

411
00:56:45,195 --> 00:56:47,489
I'll pike her in the spine.
Keep her breathing.

412
00:56:47,739 --> 00:56:48,699
No.

413
00:56:48,949 --> 00:56:50,576
Put a bullet in her skull.

414
00:56:50,826 --> 00:56:53,537
Stop the Rig, return my treasures to me...

415
00:56:53,912 --> 00:56:56,206
...and I, myself, will carry you...

416
00:56:56,832 --> 00:56:57,916
...to the Gates...

417
00:56:58,166 --> 00:56:59,418
...of Valhalla.

418
00:57:00,043 --> 00:57:01,169
Am I awaited?

419
00:57:02,045 --> 00:57:03,463
You will ride eternal...

420
00:57:03,922 --> 00:57:06,008
...shiny and chrome.

421
00:57:07,551 --> 00:57:08,719
Rictus!

422
00:57:09,469 --> 00:57:11,054
Help him aboard!

423
00:57:13,223 --> 00:57:14,056
Ready?

424
00:57:14,474 --> 00:57:15,684
Here we go!

425
00:57:27,571 --> 00:57:28,404
Mediocre!

426
00:57:59,102 --> 00:58:00,103
Schlanger!

427
00:58:21,041 --> 00:58:22,542
Look out!

428
00:58:24,836 --> 00:58:25,669
Angharad!

429
00:58:26,546 --> 00:58:27,379
Get out!

430
00:58:49,027 --> 00:58:49,860
No!

431
00:58:50,362 --> 00:58:51,195
Angharad!

432
00:59:05,836 --> 00:59:08,088
Stop! Turn the Rig around!

433
00:59:09,047 --> 00:59:10,507
Go back for her!

434
00:59:11,842 --> 00:59:12,759
No.

435
00:59:13,009 --> 00:59:14,511
Tell him to turn the Rig around!

436
00:59:14,761 --> 00:59:15,804
Did you see it?

437
00:59:16,346 --> 00:59:18,265
She went under the wheels.

438
00:59:18,515 --> 00:59:19,891
Did you see it?

439
00:59:21,560 --> 00:59:23,270
She went under the wheels.

440
00:59:24,479 --> 00:59:25,647
We keep moving.

441
00:59:25,897 --> 00:59:26,940
- No!
- We keep moving!

442
00:59:27,190 --> 00:59:29,818
He doesn't know what he's talking about!

443
00:59:30,068 --> 00:59:32,070
Whatever happens,
we're going to the Green Place.

444
00:59:32,320 --> 00:59:34,698
The stupid Green Place.
We don't even know where to find it!

445
00:59:47,335 --> 00:59:49,796
- You all right?
- On! On!

446
01:00:27,834 --> 01:00:29,044
Cheedo!

447
01:00:29,544 --> 01:00:30,962
Cheedo, don't be stupid.

448
01:00:31,213 --> 01:00:32,046
Stop!

449
01:00:32,214 --> 01:00:33,757
He'll forgive us. I know he will.

450
01:00:34,007 --> 01:00:35,175
There is no going back!

451
01:00:35,425 --> 01:00:37,093
- We were his treasures!
- Cheedo!

452
01:00:37,511 --> 01:00:40,222
We were protected!
He gave us the high life!

453
01:00:40,472 --> 01:00:43,225
- What's wrong with that?
- We are not things.

454
01:00:43,475 --> 01:00:44,308
No!

455
01:00:45,644 --> 01:00:46,645
We are not things!

456
01:00:47,145 --> 01:00:48,146
We are not things.

457
01:00:48,396 --> 01:00:51,316
- I don't want to hear that again!
- They were her words!

458
01:00:51,566 --> 01:00:52,734
And now she's dead!

459
01:00:54,152 --> 01:00:55,505
Wring your hands and tear your hair...

460
01:00:55,529 --> 01:00:56,988
...but you're not going back.

461
01:00:57,447 --> 01:00:59,241
You're not going back to him.

462
01:00:59,491 --> 01:01:00,408
Angharad!

463
01:01:00,659 --> 01:01:02,536
Come on! Come on!

464
01:01:19,719 --> 01:01:22,264
So, um, ahem...

465
01:01:22,597 --> 01:01:24,140
...where is this...

466
01:01:25,600 --> 01:01:27,227
...Green Place?

467
01:01:28,311 --> 01:01:30,480
It's a long night's run, heading east.

468
01:01:32,899 --> 01:01:34,109
We need inventory.

469
01:01:34,359 --> 01:01:35,735
Match every gun with its bullets.

470
01:01:40,866 --> 01:01:42,409
I'm gonna go and do some repairs.

471
01:01:42,659 --> 01:01:44,077
We need someone down the back.

472
01:01:44,327 --> 01:01:45,160
I'll go.

473
01:01:45,328 --> 01:01:46,161
No.

474
01:01:46,288 --> 01:01:48,039
I want you to stay together.

475
01:01:48,623 --> 01:01:49,875
I can do it.

476
01:02:22,991 --> 01:02:24,200
What are you doing here?

477
01:02:25,535 --> 01:02:26,870
He saw it.

478
01:02:27,454 --> 01:02:28,872
He saw it all.

479
01:02:30,290 --> 01:02:32,792
My own Blood Bag driving the Rig
that killed her.

480
01:02:40,550 --> 01:02:41,760
Stop doing that.

481
01:02:45,347 --> 01:02:46,431
Stop.

482
01:02:56,566 --> 01:02:59,361
Three times the gates were open to me.

483
01:02:59,653 --> 01:03:00,654
What gates?

484
01:03:01,363 --> 01:03:03,156
I was awaited in Valhalla.

485
01:03:03,490 --> 01:03:04,991
They were calling my name.

486
01:03:05,784 --> 01:03:09,537
I should be walking with the Immorta.
McFeasting with the heroes of all time.

487
01:03:12,916 --> 01:03:15,961
I'd say it was your
manifest destiny not to.

488
01:03:17,796 --> 01:03:20,465
I thought I was being spared
for something great.

489
01:03:20,715 --> 01:03:24,177
I got to drive a pursuit vehicle.

490
01:03:25,011 --> 01:03:28,139
For a while even Larry and Barry
stopped chewing on my windpipe.

491
01:03:28,515 --> 01:03:30,183
Who are Larry and Barry?

492
01:03:31,059 --> 01:03:32,310
My mates.

493
01:03:32,852 --> 01:03:34,145
Larry and Barry.

494
01:03:36,189 --> 01:03:38,775
If they don't get me,
then the Night Fevers will.

495
01:04:03,299 --> 01:04:07,095
Well, we've only got four for Big
Boy here, so he's all but useless.

496
01:04:08,555 --> 01:04:09,639
But...

497
01:04:09,889 --> 01:04:13,893
...we can squirt off this little pinky
a raunchy 29 times.

498
01:04:16,312 --> 01:04:18,440
Angharad used to call them Antiseed.

499
01:04:19,190 --> 01:04:21,609
Plant one and watch something die.

500
01:05:37,310 --> 01:05:39,437
Hold on, mate.

501
01:05:56,871 --> 01:05:59,999
We are down 30,000 units of guzzoline...

502
01:06:00,250 --> 01:06:03,128
...19 canisters of nitro,
12 assault bikes...

503
01:06:04,212 --> 01:06:05,252
...seven pursuit vehicles.

504
01:06:05,880 --> 01:06:07,006
The deficit mounts.

505
01:06:07,257 --> 01:06:08,341
And now, sir...

506
01:06:08,633 --> 01:06:11,553
...you have us stuck in a quagmire.

507
01:06:12,095 --> 01:06:13,263
Hey, Joe!

508
01:06:14,180 --> 01:06:15,265
Boss!

509
01:06:17,308 --> 01:06:19,519
Your girly's breathing her last!

510
01:06:20,145 --> 01:06:22,063
What about the child?

511
01:06:31,281 --> 01:06:32,782
Are you coming, brother?

512
01:06:33,032 --> 01:06:34,117
Wait!

513
01:06:35,243 --> 01:06:36,953
It's gone awful quiet in there.

514
01:06:37,203 --> 01:06:38,371
Get it out.

515
01:06:38,621 --> 01:06:39,873
Get it out!

516
01:06:42,709 --> 01:06:44,836
Come on! I've been called to the torture!

517
01:06:45,587 --> 01:06:46,588
Patience!

518
01:06:48,381 --> 01:06:50,884
Oh, you stay here with your grief, Daddy.

519
01:06:51,134 --> 01:06:54,304
- I'll fetch them for you.
- Be careful! Protect the assets!

520
01:06:56,931 --> 01:06:59,184
Just one angry shot...

521
01:06:59,809 --> 01:07:01,477
...for Furiosa.

522
01:07:01,728 --> 01:07:02,687
Hut!

523
01:07:02,937 --> 01:07:03,897
Yeah!

524
01:07:10,195 --> 01:07:12,655
Crying shame. Heh.

525
01:07:12,906 --> 01:07:14,032
Come.

526
01:07:15,158 --> 01:07:16,034
Another month...

527
01:07:16,993 --> 01:07:18,828
...could have been your viable human!

528
01:07:19,078 --> 01:07:20,413
Was it a male?

529
01:07:20,663 --> 01:07:22,248
Your A-1 Alpha prime.

530
01:07:25,460 --> 01:07:26,753
Hey, Rictus!

531
01:07:28,087 --> 01:07:29,797
You lost a baby brother!

532
01:07:32,258 --> 01:07:34,010
Perfect in every way.

533
01:07:36,804 --> 01:07:38,348
I had a baby brother!

534
01:07:38,765 --> 01:07:40,725
I had a little baby brother!

535
01:07:40,975 --> 01:07:42,769
And he was perfect!

536
01:07:43,019 --> 01:07:44,896
Perfect in every way!

537
01:08:15,635 --> 01:08:16,761
Come on.

538
01:08:26,104 --> 01:08:27,855
Wouldn't wanna shoot the wives, sir.

539
01:08:28,106 --> 01:08:29,190
Just probing.

540
01:08:40,535 --> 01:08:42,120
He wants to help!

541
01:08:42,370 --> 01:08:43,203
Who?

542
01:08:43,413 --> 01:08:44,747
The War Boy!

543
01:08:44,998 --> 01:08:46,416
Where did he come from?

544
01:08:46,666 --> 01:08:48,066
I thought we threw him off the Rig!

545
01:08:52,505 --> 01:08:53,506
There's high ground...

546
01:08:53,756 --> 01:08:55,676
- ...just beyond that thing.
- He means the tree.

547
01:08:55,967 --> 01:08:57,552
Yeah. Tree!

548
01:08:59,053 --> 01:08:59,886
Leave him to me.

549
01:09:00,054 --> 01:09:03,558
Say, anyone notice that bright light?
Encroaching gunfire?

550
01:09:04,183 --> 01:09:05,016
Get out.

551
01:09:05,184 --> 01:09:06,537
I can do this. I know this machine.

552
01:09:06,561 --> 01:09:08,146
He does. He's a Revhead.

553
01:09:13,735 --> 01:09:14,736
You've got two left!

554
01:09:21,117 --> 01:09:22,243
On him.

555
01:09:39,886 --> 01:09:41,471
Don't breathe.

556
01:09:45,433 --> 01:09:46,017
Hey!

557
01:09:46,267 --> 01:09:47,602
Hey! Hey!

558
01:09:47,852 --> 01:09:48,853
War Boy!

559
01:09:49,103 --> 01:09:51,689
I'm gonna use the winch
around the tree thing!

560
01:09:52,648 --> 01:09:53,775
Take this.

561
01:09:54,025 --> 01:09:55,735
Let's get the engine plates.

562
01:09:56,986 --> 01:09:57,945
You drive the Rig!

563
01:09:58,196 --> 01:10:00,031
- Hold up a flare!
- I am holding a flare!

564
01:10:00,823 --> 01:10:03,201
- Closer!
- It's right in front of your eyes!

565
01:10:15,546 --> 01:10:17,256
Hut! Hut!

566
01:10:23,638 --> 01:10:24,847
Blood Bag!

567
01:10:31,312 --> 01:10:33,689
I am the scales of justice!

568
01:10:34,023 --> 01:10:36,526
Conductor of the choir of death!

569
01:10:37,610 --> 01:10:39,404
Sing, Brother Heckler.

570
01:10:41,072 --> 01:10:42,657
Sing, Brother Koch!

571
01:10:45,618 --> 01:10:49,163
Sing, brothers, sing! Sing!

572
01:10:50,289 --> 01:10:51,849
Don't they know they're shooting at us?

573
01:11:06,389 --> 01:11:07,557
Gun fever!

574
01:12:17,835 --> 01:12:20,129
I never thought I'd do something
as shine as that.

575
01:12:20,671 --> 01:12:22,131
How are the engines?

576
01:12:22,798 --> 01:12:24,217
Very hot and real thirsty.

577
01:12:29,096 --> 01:12:33,100
Hey. You need to take the War Rig
half a klick down the track.

578
01:12:34,268 --> 01:12:37,188
What if you're not back by the time
the engines have cooled?

579
01:12:39,357 --> 01:12:40,942
Well, you keep moving.

580
01:12:50,368 --> 01:12:52,411
What do you suppose he's gonna do?

581
01:12:53,496 --> 01:12:55,039
Retaliate first.

582
01:12:58,417 --> 01:12:59,627
Let's go!

583
01:14:19,415 --> 01:14:22,001
Are you hurt?

584
01:14:22,251 --> 01:14:23,461
You're bleeding.

585
01:14:24,170 --> 01:14:25,671
That's not his blood.

586
01:14:27,465 --> 01:14:28,841
What is this?

587
01:14:29,759 --> 01:14:30,926
It's Mother's Milk.

588
01:15:13,469 --> 01:15:14,470
It's okay.

589
01:15:14,720 --> 01:15:15,763
Sleep.

590
01:15:16,972 --> 01:15:18,474
Get some rest.

591
01:15:28,943 --> 01:15:31,529
How do you know this place even exists?

592
01:15:34,198 --> 01:15:35,700
I was born there.

593
01:15:37,993 --> 01:15:39,078
So why'd you leave?

594
01:15:39,495 --> 01:15:40,663
I didn't.

595
01:15:42,248 --> 01:15:44,166
I was taken as a child.

596
01:15:45,918 --> 01:15:47,044
Stolen.

597
01:15:53,092 --> 01:15:54,802
You done this before?

598
01:15:55,469 --> 01:15:56,846
Many times.

599
01:15:57,847 --> 01:16:00,141
Now that I drive a War Rig...

600
01:16:01,726 --> 01:16:03,894
...this is the best shot I'll ever have.

601
01:16:04,979 --> 01:16:06,147
And them?

602
01:16:08,065 --> 01:16:09,692
They're looking for hope.

603
01:16:10,735 --> 01:16:12,111
What about you?

604
01:16:17,575 --> 01:16:18,868
Redemption.

605
01:17:02,328 --> 01:17:04,747
Hey, what's that?

606
01:17:17,343 --> 01:17:19,470
I remember something like that.

607
01:17:31,732 --> 01:17:33,275
Help me!

608
01:17:36,362 --> 01:17:37,947
Help me!

609
01:17:41,450 --> 01:17:42,743
Help me, please!

610
01:17:42,993 --> 01:17:44,245
Please!

611
01:17:44,954 --> 01:17:46,080
That's bait.

612
01:17:47,540 --> 01:17:48,916
Stay in the Rig.

613
01:17:54,171 --> 01:17:57,049
Hurry! Please, hurry! They'll be back!

614
01:17:58,467 --> 01:17:59,301
I am one of...

615
01:17:59,552 --> 01:18:00,803
...the Vuvalini!

616
01:18:01,762 --> 01:18:03,556
Of the Many Mothers!

617
01:18:05,140 --> 01:18:08,352
My Initiate Mother was K.T. Concannon!

618
01:18:09,520 --> 01:18:12,189
I am the daughter of Mary Jabassa.

619
01:18:13,399 --> 01:18:16,235
My clan was Swaddle Dog!

620
01:19:03,449 --> 01:19:04,742
It's me.

621
01:19:12,791 --> 01:19:14,543
There's something in the eyes.

622
01:19:15,085 --> 01:19:17,171
Perhaps it is Jabassa's child.

623
01:19:22,259 --> 01:19:23,177
This is our Furiosa.

624
01:19:26,722 --> 01:19:28,098
How long has it been?

625
01:19:29,725 --> 01:19:31,101
Seven thousand days.

626
01:19:31,727 --> 01:19:33,812
Plus the ones I don't remember.

627
01:19:35,230 --> 01:19:36,273
Furiosa.

628
01:19:37,691 --> 01:19:39,360
What happened to your mother?

629
01:19:40,819 --> 01:19:42,154
She died.

630
01:19:42,988 --> 01:19:44,657
On the third day.

631
01:19:51,830 --> 01:19:52,915
From where did you come?

632
01:19:53,290 --> 01:19:57,002
The West. Citadel. Beyond the mountains.

633
01:20:01,298 --> 01:20:02,131
The men.

634
01:20:02,174 --> 01:20:03,342
Who are they?

635
01:20:03,592 --> 01:20:04,927
They're reliable.

636
01:20:05,344 --> 01:20:07,012
They helped us get here.

637
01:20:18,899 --> 01:20:21,110
Where did you find such creatures?

638
01:20:23,696 --> 01:20:24,989
So soft.

639
01:20:25,698 --> 01:20:27,116
This one has all her teeth!

640
01:20:36,208 --> 01:20:38,335
I can't wait for them to see it.

641
01:20:38,961 --> 01:20:40,087
See?

642
01:20:41,255 --> 01:20:42,506
See what?

643
01:20:42,756 --> 01:20:44,008
Home.

644
01:20:48,012 --> 01:20:49,513
The Green Place.

645
01:20:49,763 --> 01:20:51,890
But if you came from the West...

646
01:20:52,933 --> 01:20:54,476
...you passed it.

647
01:20:55,811 --> 01:20:57,271
The crows.

648
01:20:57,563 --> 01:21:00,065
The creepy place with all the crows.

649
01:21:01,150 --> 01:21:02,484
- The soil.
- We had to get out.

650
01:21:02,735 --> 01:21:04,528
- We had no water.
- The water was filth.

651
01:21:04,778 --> 01:21:06,405
It was poisoned. It was sour.

652
01:21:06,655 --> 01:21:08,032
And then the crows came.

653
01:21:08,282 --> 01:21:10,034
We couldn't grow anything.

654
01:21:10,284 --> 01:21:11,618
Where are the others?

655
01:21:11,869 --> 01:21:12,828
What others?

656
01:21:13,078 --> 01:21:14,246
The Many Mothers.

657
01:21:14,496 --> 01:21:15,998
We're the only ones left.

658
01:22:16,934 --> 01:22:18,060
Look.

659
01:22:20,771 --> 01:22:23,023
That's what you call a satellite.

660
01:22:23,774 --> 01:22:26,026
Miss Giddy told us about those.

661
01:22:26,610 --> 01:22:29,446
They used to bounce messages
across the Earth.

662
01:22:30,239 --> 01:22:31,782
Shows.

663
01:22:32,032 --> 01:22:34,326
Everyone in the old world had a show.

664
01:22:36,662 --> 01:22:37,722
Do you think there's still...

665
01:22:37,746 --> 01:22:39,039
...somebody out there?

666
01:22:40,249 --> 01:22:41,792
Sending shows?

667
01:22:42,084 --> 01:22:43,418
Who knows?

668
01:22:44,545 --> 01:22:46,797
Those are the Plains of Silence.

669
01:22:49,424 --> 01:22:51,468
Stay right where you are, little Joe.

670
01:22:51,718 --> 01:22:53,846
Kind of lost its novelty out here.

671
01:22:54,096 --> 01:22:55,681
You having a baby?

672
01:22:56,765 --> 01:22:58,225
Warlord Junior.

673
01:22:58,475 --> 01:22:59,726
Gonna be so ugly.

674
01:23:00,352 --> 01:23:01,770
It could be a girl.

675
01:23:03,647 --> 01:23:05,232
You kill people with that, do you?

676
01:23:05,524 --> 01:23:07,568
Killed everyone I ever met out here.

677
01:23:07,818 --> 01:23:10,154
Headshots. All of them.
Snap. Right in the medulla.

678
01:23:10,404 --> 01:23:12,364
Thought somehow you girls were above that.

679
01:23:16,994 --> 01:23:18,162
Come here.

680
01:23:25,878 --> 01:23:26,879
Take a peek.

681
01:23:27,880 --> 01:23:29,131
Seeds.

682
01:23:30,132 --> 01:23:31,592
These are from home.

683
01:23:31,842 --> 01:23:34,011
Heirlooms. The real thing.

684
01:23:34,678 --> 01:23:36,513
I plant one every chance I get.

685
01:23:36,763 --> 01:23:37,764
Where?

686
01:23:38,140 --> 01:23:41,059
So far, nothing's took.
Earth's too sour.

687
01:23:41,393 --> 01:23:43,145
Aah. So many different kinds.

688
01:23:43,437 --> 01:23:45,480
Trees, flowers, fruit.

689
01:23:46,440 --> 01:23:48,567
Back then, everyone had their fill.

690
01:23:49,276 --> 01:23:51,486
Back then,
there was no need to snap anybody.

691
01:24:07,127 --> 01:24:07,961
Can I talk to you?

692
01:24:28,190 --> 01:24:30,108
I've talked with the others.

693
01:24:36,907 --> 01:24:40,160
We're never gonna have a better chance
to make it across the salt.

694
01:24:42,329 --> 01:24:46,333
If we leave the Rig here, and load the
motorcycles up with as much as we can...

695
01:24:46,583 --> 01:24:49,086
...we can maybe ride for 160 days.

696
01:24:51,797 --> 01:24:53,757
One of those bikes is yours.

697
01:24:54,883 --> 01:24:56,134
Fully loaded.

698
01:24:59,263 --> 01:25:01,431
You're more than welcome to come with us.

699
01:25:05,435 --> 01:25:07,396
I'll make my own way.

700
01:25:14,069 --> 01:25:16,154
You know, hope is a mistake.

701
01:25:23,036 --> 01:25:26,331
If you can't fix what's broken,
you'll, uh...

702
01:25:28,292 --> 01:25:29,876
You'll go insane.

703
01:25:46,059 --> 01:25:47,686
<i>Where are you, Max?</i>

704
01:25:49,730 --> 01:25:51,023
<i>Where are you?</i>

705
01:25:52,649 --> 01:25:54,693
<i>Help us. You promised to help us.</i>

706
01:26:05,120 --> 01:26:07,372
<i>Come on, Pa! Let's go.</i>

707
01:26:39,321 --> 01:26:40,405
All right.

708
01:26:41,740 --> 01:26:43,909
This is your way home.

709
01:26:47,412 --> 01:26:48,455
We go back?

710
01:26:50,707 --> 01:26:52,501
- Back?
- Yeah.

711
01:26:52,751 --> 01:26:54,461
I thought you weren't insane anymore.

712
01:26:54,711 --> 01:26:55,921
What are they saying?

713
01:26:56,171 --> 01:26:58,382
He wants to go back from where they came.

714
01:26:58,632 --> 01:26:59,800
The Citadel.

715
01:27:00,550 --> 01:27:02,219
What's there to find at the Citadel?

716
01:27:02,969 --> 01:27:04,179
Green.

717
01:27:04,429 --> 01:27:05,764
And water.

718
01:27:07,015 --> 01:27:10,894
There's a ridiculous amount of
clear water. And a lot of crops.

719
01:27:11,144 --> 01:27:13,584
Got everything you need.
Long as you're not afraid of heights.

720
01:27:13,814 --> 01:27:15,054
Where does the water come from?

721
01:27:15,190 --> 01:27:18,860
He pumps it up from deep in the earth. Calls
it Aqua Cola and claims it for himself.

722
01:27:19,111 --> 01:27:21,363
And because he owns it, he owns all of us.

723
01:27:21,613 --> 01:27:22,781
I don't like him already.

724
01:27:23,031 --> 01:27:25,409
It'll take two weeks
to skirt the Wall of Mountains.

725
01:27:25,659 --> 01:27:26,576
No.

726
01:27:26,827 --> 01:27:29,538
I suggest we go back the same way we came.

727
01:27:31,081 --> 01:27:32,666
Through the canyon.

728
01:27:33,708 --> 01:27:37,587
It's open. We know that. Right?
He brought all his war parties through.

729
01:27:38,088 --> 01:27:41,466
So we take the War Rig and we charge it
right through the middle of them.

730
01:27:41,716 --> 01:27:42,876
We can decouple the tanker...

731
01:27:42,968 --> 01:27:44,219
...at the pass.

732
01:27:44,594 --> 01:27:46,096
Shut it off behind us.

733
01:27:46,346 --> 01:27:47,472
Kaboom.

734
01:27:50,308 --> 01:27:52,853
And how exactly do we take the Citadel?

735
01:27:53,395 --> 01:27:55,188
Assuming we're still alive by then.

736
01:27:55,439 --> 01:27:58,024
If we can block the pass, it'll be easy.

737
01:27:58,275 --> 01:28:02,028
All that's left are his War Pups
and War Boys too sick to fight.

738
01:28:02,737 --> 01:28:04,489
And we'll be with Nux.

739
01:28:05,157 --> 01:28:06,366
He's a War Boy.

740
01:28:06,616 --> 01:28:09,496
He'll be bringing us home. Bringing
back what's stolen, as he's meant to.

741
01:28:12,664 --> 01:28:13,832
Yeah.

742
01:28:14,791 --> 01:28:16,376
It feels like hope.

743
01:28:17,586 --> 01:28:19,129
I like this plan.

744
01:28:19,713 --> 01:28:20,714
We can start again.

745
01:28:21,381 --> 01:28:23,049
Just like the old days!

746
01:28:24,634 --> 01:28:25,844
Look.

747
01:28:26,553 --> 01:28:28,263
It'll be a hard day.

748
01:28:28,722 --> 01:28:31,808
But I guarantee you
that a 160 days' ride that way...

749
01:28:34,144 --> 01:28:36,188
...there's nothing but salt.

750
01:28:38,648 --> 01:28:41,526
At least that way, you know,
we might be able to...

751
01:28:43,028 --> 01:28:44,279
...together...

752
01:28:45,864 --> 01:28:47,949
...come across some kind of redemption.

753
01:29:18,730 --> 01:29:20,106
War Rig!

754
01:29:20,398 --> 01:29:22,317
That's the War Rig!

755
01:29:32,327 --> 01:29:33,537
That's them.

756
01:29:33,787 --> 01:29:35,038
Why are they going back?

757
01:29:35,497 --> 01:29:37,165
Do they wish to surrender?

758
01:29:37,874 --> 01:29:39,376
They are heading for the canyon.

759
01:29:41,253 --> 01:29:44,214
They're going back to the Citadel!

760
01:29:44,464 --> 01:29:46,132
They know it's undefended!

761
01:29:46,383 --> 01:29:47,467
Bollocks!

762
01:29:48,843 --> 01:29:49,970
Roll up!

763
01:30:00,272 --> 01:30:01,523
Go!

764
01:30:23,878 --> 01:30:25,380
- What are you doing?
- Praying.

765
01:30:25,630 --> 01:30:26,590
To who?

766
01:30:26,840 --> 01:30:28,300
Anyone that's listening.

767
01:30:52,699 --> 01:30:53,658
Here we go, girls!

768
01:30:56,328 --> 01:30:57,579
That's mine!

769
01:31:01,958 --> 01:31:03,918
He'll try to get in front of us.
Spike our wheels.

770
01:31:11,217 --> 01:31:12,260
Don't blow my engine.

771
01:31:12,802 --> 01:31:13,803
Gonna nudge him.

772
01:31:14,054 --> 01:31:15,138
Just a little.

773
01:31:28,109 --> 01:31:31,071
You filth! You traitored him!

774
01:31:35,950 --> 01:31:36,783
Yeah!

775
01:31:55,095 --> 01:31:55,928
Go.

776
01:32:22,288 --> 01:32:23,121
Gotta back off.

777
01:32:23,998 --> 01:32:26,418
Engine one is gone.
Two's about to blow.

778
01:32:26,668 --> 01:32:27,501
Right.

779
01:32:28,169 --> 01:32:29,087
Are you a Black Thumb?

780
01:32:30,630 --> 01:32:31,881
All right. Engine one. Now.

781
01:32:32,132 --> 01:32:33,466
You and me. Fifth wheel.

782
01:32:33,883 --> 01:32:35,009
We'll unhook the tanker.

783
01:32:47,647 --> 01:32:48,565
One man, one bullet.

784
01:33:06,541 --> 01:33:08,168
- I cannot see.
- Maadi! Maadi!

785
01:33:08,418 --> 01:33:09,586
I can't see.

786
01:33:49,000 --> 01:33:49,959
Hey!

787
01:33:50,210 --> 01:33:51,711
Harpoons and plows!

788
01:33:52,128 --> 01:33:53,338
They're hauling us back!

789
01:34:04,599 --> 01:34:06,810
Leave three bolts. Three.

790
01:35:25,346 --> 01:35:26,179
Hey, you! Aargh!

791
01:35:41,988 --> 01:35:43,281
Are you okay?

792
01:35:45,992 --> 01:35:47,619
I think she's hurt.

793
01:36:11,476 --> 01:36:12,309
Hey!

794
01:36:38,628 --> 01:36:39,461
No!

795
01:36:43,591 --> 01:36:44,550
No!

796
01:36:49,389 --> 01:36:50,723
<i>Hey.</i>

797
01:36:51,265 --> 01:36:52,098
<i>Stay with me.</i>

798
01:36:52,517 --> 01:36:54,268
<i>- Stay with me.</i>
- Stay with me.

799
01:36:54,519 --> 01:36:55,895
<i>- Hey.</i>
- Hey! Are you there?

800
01:36:57,772 --> 01:36:59,092
You finish that! I'll finish her!

801
01:38:29,614 --> 01:38:30,447
Valhalla!

802
01:39:11,322 --> 01:39:12,156
Engine one's good.

803
01:39:13,282 --> 01:39:14,450
For now.

804
01:40:02,665 --> 01:40:04,083
She's hurt! She's hurt...

805
01:40:04,333 --> 01:40:05,376
...real bad!

806
01:41:35,758 --> 01:41:36,591
You hear that?

807
01:41:37,426 --> 01:41:39,011
We're gonna see two airborne V8s.

808
01:41:40,554 --> 01:41:42,265
I'm gonna need you to drive.

809
01:41:44,475 --> 01:41:46,143
I'll get him out of our way.

810
01:42:53,169 --> 01:42:54,462
Rictus!

811
01:42:55,546 --> 01:42:56,380
Take me!

812
01:43:09,977 --> 01:43:10,810
Cheedo!

813
01:43:10,978 --> 01:43:12,521
- What are you doing?
- Good girl.

814
01:43:16,859 --> 01:43:17,985
Come here.

815
01:43:23,407 --> 01:43:24,283
Big Boy!

816
01:43:30,539 --> 01:43:32,375
Here! Here!

817
01:44:26,262 --> 01:44:27,430
Remember me?

818
01:44:48,784 --> 01:44:49,827
He's dead!

819
01:44:50,661 --> 01:44:51,829
He's dead.

820
01:45:10,848 --> 01:45:13,809
When you're across safe,
I'll jam the throttle and follow you.

821
01:45:14,602 --> 01:45:15,644
Come on!

822
01:45:16,729 --> 01:45:19,273
Hurry! We're nearly at the pass.

823
01:46:06,904 --> 01:46:08,489
Witness me.

824
01:46:14,954 --> 01:46:15,955
Rictus!

825
01:47:11,552 --> 01:47:13,178
Why is she making that noise?

826
01:47:13,429 --> 01:47:15,139
She's pumping air into her chest cavity.

827
01:47:16,015 --> 01:47:17,558
She's collapsing her lungs...

828
01:47:17,808 --> 01:47:19,602
...one breath at a time.

829
01:47:25,357 --> 01:47:26,525
I know.

830
01:47:29,486 --> 01:47:30,946
I am so sorry.

